# CODEOWNERS for letya999/ai-repo-safety-skill
#
# GitHub CODEOWNERS gates pull-request approvals to the listed
# teams/users for the matched paths. See
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# This file is the social complement to the SHA-pinning convention
# used in .github/workflows/*.yml: even if a SHA pin is correct,
# a malicious or careless change to a workflow file should require
# explicit review by the security maintainer before it can land.
#
# Replace @letya999/maintainers below with the actual team slug
# or user handles that the maintainer wants to gate on. The
# placeholder string intentionally fails closed (no matching
# owners) so that the file does not silently grant ownership to
# the wrong account.

# All workflow files must be reviewed by the security maintainer.
/.github/workflows/   @letya999/maintainers
/.github/actions/      @letya999/maintainers

# Security-sensitive generated assets that ship inside the wheel.
/src/ai_repo_safety/assets/templates/  @letya999/maintainers
/src/ai_repo_safety/assets/rules/        @letya999/maintainers
/src/ai_repo_safety/assets/scripts/     @letya999/maintainers
/src/ai_repo_safety/assets/agents/      @letya999/maintainers

# Pre-commit, Renovate, and OpenCode configuration are security
# load-bearing; require the same review.
/.pre-commit-config.ai-repo-safety.yaml  @letya999/maintainers
/renovate.json                          @letya999/maintainers
/AGENTS.md                              @letya999/maintainers
/SECURITY.md                            @letya999/maintainers
/CHANGELOG.md                           @letya999/maintainers

# Default catch-all so any file the maintainer adds later also
# requires explicit ownership. Loosen this to a public team if
# outside contributions become common.
/*   @letya999/maintainers
